This topic tells you how to resolve common errors that arise when configuring a single sign-on
partnership between PingFederate and <%= vars.product_full %>.

##<a id='error'></a> Error

### Symptom

You see an error similar to the following screenshot:

<%= image_tag('../images/error_pingfederate.png', :alt => "The error message page reads,
Unexpected System Error. Sorry for the inconvenience. Please contact your administrator
for assistance and provide the reference number below to help locate and correct the
problem. Reference #: cfyfvn.") %>

### Explanation

Possible explanations are as follows:

- Connection Status is deactivated on PingFederate.

- The service provider Entity ID is misconfigured on PingFederate.

- The identity provider Single Sign-On URL is misconfigured in the <%= vars.product_short %> plan settings.

##<a id="no-metadata"></a> Metadata Not Found

### Symptom

You see an error similar to the following screenshot:

<%= image_tag('../images/pingfederate_error_metadata_not_found.png',
:alt => "The error message page reads, Metadata for issuer wasn't found.") %>

### Explanation

The identity provider Entity ID is misconfigured in the <%= vars.product_short %> plan settings.
